<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="leading-adj">leading <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'liːdɪŋ/    美 /'liːdɪŋ/  </p>
<p>[只用于名词前]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>最好的；最重要的；最成功的</strong></h4>
<p>best, most important or most successful：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a leading expert
最好的专家</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A fueling ambition plays a leading role in one's success.
不断增长的抱负在一个人的成功中起着主要作用。</p><footer>2009 上海</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>领先的；前列的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In the rice-growing world, the Chinese scientist, Yuan Longping, is a <strong>leading figure</strong>. 
在水稻种植领域，中国科学家袁隆平是一位领军人物。</p><footer>外研④ – 4</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the leading runners in the race
比赛中跑在前面的人</p></div></div>